PartialCountyJustification: HAP is collaborating with health systems for its narrow network QHPs that have demonstrated outcomes of high quality patient care, commitment to transparency in measuring and reporting the quality of patient care provided to QHP enrollees and delivering care through a clinical model that promotes clinical integration and care coordination to improve quality, patient satisfaction and the enrolled population?s health status. HAP cannot identify additional health systems that satisfy these criteria and would materially improve access in the limited portions of northwestern Oakland County identified as not sufficient by DIFS. Absent a health system that meets these criteria ? and despite having sufficient ancillary and physician providers - HAP cannot contract with sufficient hospital providers to serve all of Oakland County. HAP has decided to not offer its High Performing Network QHPs in these areas not because of any population differences or other factors, demographic, socio-economic or otherwise, in this area.  Rather, DIFS review suggests hospital access to our High Performing Network is not sufficient in the excluded areas of northwest Oakland County.
